{"TopicId":57717,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"Fully Functional Bipedal Mech","CreatedByName":"SoldierHair","CreatedById":62167,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-25T19:05:23Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SoldierHair","CreatedById":62167,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-25T19:05:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EMade this in a day of work.The thing i like the most about it is the cupola shield.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/x2E9pJrsKb4?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003EObviously you need Lazor\u0027s Mods and Infernal Robotics to use it.And possibly KW Rocketry too.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt\u0027s the first mech i ever build, hope you like it!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://dfiles.eu/files/pwbff47pi\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://dfiles.eu/files/pwbff47pi\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WhiteWeasel","CreatedById":59171,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-26T00:26:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThat\u0027s insane. Amazing engineering skills. Video Becomes an order of magnitude more awesome with this song in the background.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/blCBoXKCGl0?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-12-26T00:29:31Z\u0022 title=\u002212/26/2013 12:29  AM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 26, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by WhiteWeasel\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SoldierHair","CreatedById":62167,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-26T12:26:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIf anybody wants to make their own:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/-O1Od1N9cpk?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf one rotor is going clockwise, the other one should go counter-clockwise.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheTsar52","CreatedById":61707,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-26T16:28:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ESorry Katyusha, mechs ain\u0027t allowed in Tankery. Other than that small issue, \u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img.pandawhale.com/40289-Mother-of-God-OMZp.jpeg\u0022 alt=\u002240289-Mother-of-God-OMZp.jpeg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlso, I bet if you put each leg on a rotate disk thing, you could make it change direction by moving the leg side to side. That probably made no sense.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-12-26T17:27:22Z\u0022 title=\u002212/26/2013 05:27  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 26, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by TheTsar52\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SoldierHair","CreatedById":62167,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-26T18:03:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EOh, that\u0027s not for Sensha-Do.Nonna and I are also part of the Mechanics Enthusiasts club.Why do you think i\u0027m in charge of the KV-2?Because it\u0027s big and compensates for my height?Haha, oh, no.That thing requires a lot of maintenance.Once we tried to shoot to the side while climbing a hill.Ha, the gunner was knocked unconscious and the turret ring was almost destroyed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBTW\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThat thing is a whopping 400-something parts, 384 without hands.And i\u0027m surprised i managed to record at 20 FPS.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheTsar52","CreatedById":61707,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-26T18:52:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIf you shoot it with T30 (Best anti-JS-2 tank), does it survive? What is the damage taking capability? \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlso, I would put those tiny SRBs on the arms to help them not get in the way of the feet.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-12-26T19:52:54Z\u0022 title=\u002212/26/2013 07:52  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 26, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by TheTsar52\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SoldierHair","CreatedById":62167,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-12-27T10:31:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EOh, wow T30 is a bit harsh.My thing has 3 layers of 20mm plates angled at ~45 degrees at most.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-12-27T10:42:56Z\u0022 title=\u002212/27/2013 10:42  AM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 27, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by SoldierHair\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}